name: Momo's
directions: bathrooms in the back. no gender assignments.
comment: probably should buy a drink, but they might not care.

name: Mary Maxim
directions: Just to the right of the puzzle department (which is straight ahead when you enter)
comment: The building is open from 10-6.

name: Eastburn
directions: Restrooms are in side hallway, secluded from main room.
comment: Customers only.

name: Ranchos Cocina
directions: at back of restraunt
comment: customers only

name: Sound Table
directions: Two WCs on the back on the right
comment: In a bar/club environment. Buy a drink first.

name: Half Price Books Lynnwood
directions: Two single occupancy locking restrooms with changing stations in the back of the store.
comment: Restrooms are open to the public. It's a busy store so sometimes there can be a wait.

name: Bilbo Coffee Co
directions: There are two restrooms - one is in the back and requires going down a short flight of stairs, but the other is accessible by the ramp by the front entrance.

name: Ippolito's Italian restaurant
directions: Downstairs

name: Midtown Community Yoga
directions: In the back, through the doorway behind the check-in desk.

name: Moo Dang
comment: As this is in a restaurant, I imagine they don't want non-customers to use their restroom.

name: The Holland Project
directions: In the curtained area in the hallway between the gallery and show spaces.

name: Morrisons Wymondham
directions: On the far left of the store as you enter. Has baby changing facilities

name: Miso sweet
directions: First floor, large single stall bathroom

name: Caribou Coffee
directions: Must ask for key at counter but is single occupancy. Often key is just sitting on counter so don't actually have to ask.
comment: "paying customer", browse mugs and stuff a bit and you'll be fine

name: Black Eye/White Lies
directions: Hallway to the left, just before the bar.
comment: You probably have to be a paying customer.

name: Things From Another World
comment: Officially customers only, but they're pretty cool if you at least browse a little.

name: Bellevue Square
directions: 1st floor: down the center of the mall, in about the center of the floor. Down the hallway with a sign for the women's room, it's on the right just before the entrance to the women's bathroom

name: YWCA Midtown
directions: Across from locker rooms, two single occupancy "all gender" restrooms on first floor. Also have all gender locker room.
comment: Have to be a member or guest of a member to access

name: 33 Acres Brewing Company
directions: Down the hall to the left of the growler fill station when you walk in.
comment: The bathroom door simply says washroom. I'm not certain about the width of the door frame for wheelchair accessibility but there are no stairs involved and the front door is definitely accessible.

name: NuVibe
directions: In the back, to the left of the cash register

name: AMC Southcenter 16
directions: Located on 3rd Floor
comment: Large single-stall accessible, gender-neutral, family bathroom. There is also a changing table in the bathroom. It is located in the movie theater past where they collect the tickets so you probably need to be seeing a movie, but maybe you could just ask to use the bathroom. Or get a stub from someone leaving a movie to go in and use it?

name: Collegetown Bagels
directions: In the back of the seating area on the other side from where you order. Walk toward the mirror, thought the doorway, it's the door on the left.

name: Apple Walnut Street
directions: Second floor on the right near the exit sign
comment: 2 restrooms are single occupancy and there is sometimes a line.

name: Quail Ridge Books
directions: Straight in the back
comment: There is a multi-stall women's restroom and a single-stall gender neutral restroom. The store is also a safe space for all, so any transwomen in the women's bathroom will not be subjected to discrimination by staff members.

name: Trobridges Ice Cream Bar
directions: Through the first small kitchen in the back and on your immediate right
comment: Just walk right on to it, they don't mind.

name: Fitchburg Public Library
directions: 2nd floor in the back corner next to the computer lab.

name: Fun
directions: Past the tables, blue door to the right

name: Souths Bar
directions: Down the stairs!
comment: Paying customers

name: Souths bar and restaurant
directions: Down the stairs
comment: Customers!

name: American Univeristy
directions: In the first floor of all residence halls is a gender neutral bathroom. There are some scattered throughout campus mixed with gendered bathrooms. If in dorms there is also an option to make bathrooms gender neutral.

name: 5 Guys Burger and Fries
directions: Under the big "Restrooms" sign
comment: Single stalled gendered bathrooms

name: New Dorp Library
directions: On your right when you walk in the front door

name: Center for Architecture and Design
directions: Back of the first floor. Gendered restrooms welcoming. Also one Individual restroom between them.
comment: Open when Center is open to the public. Sometimes closed for private events.

name: Belmont Library
directions: get key at the desk, restrooms are on the left side of the building

name: Than Thao Restaurant
comment: It's a small family restaurant, so they would probably like you to buy something, but they are really nice

name: Brandeis University, Shapiro Campus Center
directions: Either the second or third floor, I can't remember. It's sort of tucked away

name: Café Nero
directions: Around the corner from the counter to the right in the corner
comment: They tend to be pretty relaxed about anyone using the toilet. If it's busy they won't even notice if you don't get a drink as there as seats round the corner which you could be checking to see if you can sit in.

name: Edmonton Public Library West Henday Branch
directions: Two rooms just inside the branch
comment: Hours are a bit odd: 10-6 Monday Wednesday Friday Saturday, 1-9 Tuesday Thursday, 1-5 Sunday

name: Georgetown Neighborhood Library
directions: Two single-stall restrooms on 2nd floor of library (near computer lab). Locked with a bolt and a key that you take into the restroom with you -- locate the keys on the bookshelf next to the door. Library is open 9:30am-9pm Mon-Wed, 1-9pm Thursday, 9:30am-5:30pm Fri/Sat, and 1-5pm Sun. Ask a member of library staff for assistance as needed.
comment: All single-stall restrooms in DC public libraries and all other public buildings are required to be officially gender-neutral and available for any person to use at any time, no questions asked. Restrooms that do not comply can be reported!

name: Kennebunkport Inn
directions: In the back hallway, behind the stairwell

name: Bannister Street Toilets
directions: Behind "The Warehouse Stationery" and across the road from "Evan's"
comment: Clean, manned toilets, unisex. Also with a waiting area. Shower facilities and wheelchair accessible.

name: Acworth Public Library
directions: Next to the Adult Fiction section; follow the big pink sign hanging from the ceiling that says RESTROOM -->

name: Olney Theatre Center
directions: Historic lobby, to the left of the box office, in between men and women's restrooms
comment: bathroom ostensibly for theatre patrons, but you can come in when box office is open and use without being noticed. If need be, plenty of brochures in lobby to pick up as a reason for being in the lobby.

name: Queens Library at Broadway
directions: Downstairs
comment: You have to get the keys, which are gendered, from the front desk

name: Sekend Sun (Bar)
directions: Right next to the bar, not in the basement with the other bathrooms

name: Sekend Sun (Bar)
directions: Right next to the bar, not in the basement with the other bathrooms

name: South Beach/Dunkin Donuts
directions: On the left wall, next to counter
comment: Pretty busy place, good idea to buy something

name: Hebrew College
directions: Down the side of the building by the library. To the right as you walk in that side door.
comment: School is only open weekdays and Friday until about 3pm.

name: Peet's Coffee and Tea
directions: By the counter on the left
comment: Their coffee is amazing

name: LeBauer Park
directions: Behind the play park
comment: This is marked with both genders & families

name: Momiji Restaurant
directions: At the top of the stairs

name: Boston City Hall
directions: 5th floor, Mayor's Offfice to the left of the elevators
comment: City Hall is a public building so you can just walk in and take the elevator to the 5th floor!

name: 115 E 1300 S, Salt Lake City, UT 84115, USA
directions: Back of restaurant, past the booths

name: Marquand Library
directions: Third Floor restrooms are gender-neutral (and all staff and student workers are informed of this), although Facilities has yet to change the sign
comment: To enter the library you must have Princeton ID or an Access Card, which can only be acquired in another building and might not be free so it may not be worth your trouble

name: Boojum
directions: In the back, beside the till
comment: Marked for paying customers only, the store is narrow, I don't know if a wheelchair will fit through

name: Miami University King Library
directions: Third floor go straight down the hallway until it dead ends into the Digital Collections Offices. Then turn right. The all gendered single stall restroom is between the male and female restrooms
comment: The third floor of the library is only opened from 8-5

name: Wright State University student union
directions: Go to the smoothie shop in the cafeteria; go down the nearby stairs. Restrooms should be nearby. One accessible stall per restroom.
comment: Two gendered restrooms converted into unisex.

name: Just Us Cafe
directions: Turn left after the cafe counter.
comment: You can use this washroom even if you are not a paying customer.

name: Kearns Library
directions: Both public restrooms are gender neutral. You ask for a key at the librarian's desk.

name: Bi-Partisan Cafe
directions: Back on the place

name: First United Methodist Church of Olympia
directions: Main Level near offices

name: First United Methodist Church of Olympia
directions: Two single stall room located on the main level by offices and near classrooms.

name: Kiwanis Thrift Store
directions: First floor by the books
comment: Only open Saturdays 9-12.

name: R. dos Autonomistas, 107 - Centro, Ribeirão Pires - SP, 09402-520, Brazil
Guelph Collegiate Vocational Institute
directions: Top floor, corner near the outdoor basketball court, near room 215.
comment: Presumably just for students and teachers

name: University of South Florida Saint Petersburg– University Student Center
directions: On the right wall facing cafeteria, beside The Cove
comment: There are 'men' and 'women' bathrooms, as well as a 'gender neutral' single stall. Low-moderate visibility.

name: Kazza "Wine"
directions: Bathroom is in the back.
comment:
There's no bar for handicap accessibility but there is a ramp to get in. 

The staff is very friendly and helpful. Pride ribbon in the window and very LGBT friendly environment

name: Aaron Cutler Memorial Library
directions: Entry level
comment: Open to the public

name: Pressed Cafe
directions: Back right corner near the espresso bar.
comment: Two independent rooms available. Both are gender neutral.

name: The Spot
comment: They're super chill in here. Love them!

name: Organize Now
directions: We are located near the corner of Magnolia & East Colonial. Enter through the front door.
comment: We are a grassroots community organization that dedicates itself to fighting for justice & equality. We believe that people and planet should always come before profit.

name: Haverford College Libraries
directions: all of the bathrooms are gender neutral, including on the first floor back by Special Collections
comment: Extensive hours during the school year, but keycard access only during some night hours.

name: Breaking New Grounds
comment: There are two right next to each other

name: Brixham
directions: Just before the beach and right next to the restaurant. There are 2 stalls.
comment: They are free

name: Brixham
directions: Just past the RNLI. They are public toilets.

name: Brixham
directions: Just past the RNLI. They are public toilets.

name: Cafe du Coin
directions: Up the floor and opposite the kitchen. From the front door just turn to the right.
comment: You have to be a paying customer it seems but service is quick so just get a drink maybe (or tap water - a glass is free in England and I assume it's the same here in France)

name: Marmadukes Cafe Deli

comment: You probably have to be a paying customer (I didn't check, sorry) but if in doubt just get a glass of tap water (it's free) and go right ahead. Or just grab a can of Coca Cola or something.

name: Springvale train station
directions: Just on your right after you walk through the gate, pretty hard to miss
comment: You have to tap your myki on or ask the person at the information desk to let you in

name: Diablo Gymnastics School
street: 2411 Old Crow Canyon Road Suite J
directions: Under the loft viewing area.

name: Marriott library
directions: 2nd floor across from reference desk

name: Dominican University Library
directions: Second floor, upstairs from the lobby, two single stalls
comment: Open to the public, ask the librarian at the desk for directions if you need help :)

name: First Way Plaza (general office space)
directions: On both first and second floors
